    "It comprises compounds from GNPS 52, MassBank 53, and NIST 17 (commercial, National Institute for Standards and Technology, Tandem Mass Spectral Library, 2017 release).",
    "Note that NIST17 is not public but very frequently used to train machine learning models.",
    "The dataset underwent several rounds of manual validation, discarding numerous molecular structures in the process 97,98.",
    "In total, the dataset contains 18,848 unique molecular structures.",
    "It is different from the other datasets in that it is not one public dataset but rather, a union of different spectral libraries."
